    About the Auth Server:
    You MUST NEVER edit/change/modify any part of this project, or create a
    derivative work with the purpose of bypassing the Cyan's Global Auth Server.
    Hosting a server that bypasses the CGAS (Cyan's Global Auth Server), is an
    illicit activity, and it clearly breaks the Uru client End User License
    Agreement.

    About Cracking:
    You MUST NEVER edit/change/modify any part of this project, or create a
    derivative work with the purpose of: causing damage, exploiting,
    manipulating, destroying, causing a denegation of the service, intrusion,
    or anything else with illicit results to any Plasma or Alcugs Uru servers;
    causing damage, exploiting, manipulating, destroying, causing a denegation
    of the service, intrusion, or anything else with illicit results to any
    client running any version of the Uru Clients.
    You can ignore the above notice ONLY if YOU ARE THE ADMINISTRATOR/OWNER of
    the shard or you have written permission from the shard owner and you are
    the owner of any connected client/system or you have written permission from
    the owners of all the connected clients/systems.
    All exploits, and security holes discovered must be immediately notified
    to the Alcugs H'uru server team for the immediate creation of a fix for
    the specific hole.

